## 4. Carrier Account Architecture

### The Two Modes — Official Cactus Terminology

**`lassoed_carrier_account`**
WMS/OMS integrated. Cactus has full visibility at label print.
Shipments flow through rating engine → `shipment_ledger` row created.
Full reconciliation available.
Invoice matching: PRIMARY = tracking_number → shipment_ledger

**`dark_carrier_account`**
Client entered Cactus credentials directly into their own platform
(e.g. ShipStation). Zero Cactus visibility at label print.
Shipments only enter system when carrier invoice is uploaded.
No reconciliation — billing only.
Invoice matching: PRIMARY = ship_from_address_normalized → locations

### The is_cactus_account Flag
- `TRUE` (default): Cactus earns margin. Apply markup. Generate revenue.
- `FALSE`: Pass-through account. No owned revenue. Process for
  records only. Skip markup calculation entirely.
This flag lives on `org_carrier_accounts`, not on invoices.

### Carrier Account Hierarchy
```
organizations
    └── org_carrier_accounts  (one per carrier the org uses)
            ├── markup_percentage  ← PRIMARY markup
            ├── dispute_threshold  ← per-account variance limit
            ├── carrier_account_mode (lassoed or dark)
            ├── is_cactus_account
            └── rate_cards (optional — zero or many)
                    ├── service_level (e.g. GROUND_ADVANTAGE)
                    ├── nickname
                    └── custom rate pricing
```

