## 5. Invoice Pipeline — The Billing Brain

### Full Flow
```
Carrier sends CSV/XLSX invoice weekly
        ↓
Caleb uploads in The Alamo
        ↓
AI normalizes headers → Cactus Standard fields
        ↓
Human review queue (approve/correct AI suggestions)
        ↓
For each line item:
  Look up carrier account → check carrier_account_mode

  IF lassoed_carrier_account:
    Match tracking_number → shipment_ledger → org_id
    Compare carrier_charge vs quoted_rate
    IF variance > dispute_threshold → HELD + dispute_flag = TRUE
    ELSE → apply markup → Single-Ceiling → billing_status = APPROVED

  IF dark_carrier_account:
    Normalize ship_from_address
    Match → locations.normalized_address (is_billing_address = TRUE)
    IF one match → assign org_id → apply markup → Single-Ceiling
    IF zero matches → FLAGGED "Unknown address"
    IF multiple matches → FLAGGED "Address collision"
    Create shipment_ledger row (shipment_source = INVOICE_IMPORT)
        ↓
Generate cactus_invoices from APPROVED invoice_line_items
        ↓
Sync to QuickBooks Online (qbo_invoice_id)
```

### Address Normalization Standard
All addresses must be normalized before storage and matching.
Format: `"1234 MAIN ST, PHOENIX, AZ, 85001, US"`
Rules: uppercase, abbreviate street type (ST not STREET),
use state abbreviation, strip unit/suite for matching purposes.

### 3PL Billing Rule
Cactus always bills the 3PL org directly.
3PLs bill their own merchants — that is Phase 2.
Never attempt to split a 3PL invoice across sub-clients in Phase 1.

