## 7. Database Standards (v1.3.0 — 16 Tables)

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `organizations` | Tenant root |
| `org_users` | Auth → org mapping (RLS anchor) |
| `locations` | Org addresses. Multiple per org. Billing match for dark accounts. |
| `org_carrier_accounts` | Carrier account profile. Markup lives here. |
| `rate_cards` | Optional custom rates. Children of org_carrier_accounts. |
| `meters` | USPS postage wallet |
| `meter_transactions` | Immutable meter ledger |
| `carrier_invoice_mappings` | Normalization layer (versioned + AI) |
| `shipment_ledger` | One row per shipment. Single-Ceiling output. |
| `carrier_invoices` | Uploaded invoice batch tracking |
| `invoice_line_items` | Individual carrier invoice lines. Full lifecycle. |
| `cactus_invoices` | Client-facing weekly invoices |
| `cactus_invoice_line_items` | Junction: invoices ↔ line items |
| `rate_shop_log` | Shadow Ledger — AI training dataset |
| `shipment_events` | Event sourcing timeline |
| `audit_logs` | Append-only action log |

### Supported Carriers (Phase 1)
`UPS` | `FEDEX` | `USPS` | `DHL_ECOM` | `DHL_EXPRESS` |
`UNIUNI` | `LANDMARK` | `ONTRAC` | `LSO`

### Privacy — Never expose to Cactus Portal
`raw_carrier_cost` | `markup_percentage` | `markup_flat_fee` |
`pre_ceiling_amount` | `org_carrier_accounts` data | `rate_cards` data

