## 8. Product Architecture

### The Two Portals
**Cactus Portal** — client-facing
Shipments, tracking, meter balance, invoices, AI insights.
Never shows markup, raw costs, or carrier account details.

**The Alamo** — internal Cactus admin only
- Org management (create/edit orgs, carrier accounts, rate cards)
- Invoice upload + AI normalization + human review queue
- Dispute review and resolution
- Rate card management
- Audit log viewer
- Global meter health monitor
- Carrier scorecard dashboard (Phase 2)

### Phase 1 Build Sequence
```
Stage 1: Schema v1.3.0 (complete)
Stage 2: The Alamo shell (Next.js, auth, navigation)
Stage 3: The Alamo org management (orgs, carrier accounts, rate cards)
Stage 4: The Alamo invoice pipeline (upload, normalize, match, bill)
Stage 5: Rating engine core (billing math, rate card lookup)
Stage 6: UPS + FedEx API integrations
Stage 7: Warehance WMS integration
Stage 8: Cactus Portal (client dashboard)
Post-launch: USPS + UniUni carrier integrations
```

