## 9. Coding Philosophy

### Human-First, AI-Assisted
Every non-obvious block needs a WHY comment, not just a what.

### Error Handling — Safe Fallbacks
Rate card / carrier account lookup failure must never halt
label production. Always log to audit_logs with full context.

### Idempotency
Every label purchase and meter reload must include
`idempotency_key`. Return previous result if key seen twice.

### Performance Targets
- Rating API: < 500ms
- Label purchase: < 2000ms
- Dashboard queries: < 1000ms
- Shadow Ledger writes: async, never block rating response

---

## 10. Security Standards
- API keys in `.env` only — never hardcoded
- `.env` always in `.gitignore` — never committed to GitHub
- Payment method tokens only — raw card data never in Cactus
- Service role key — backend only, never exposed to browser
- Carrier credentials — never stored in plain text
- All timestamps: `TIMESTAMPTZ`

